### 2. Filter Operators by Property Type

Filters are chained methods on the query builder. The method name is formed as:

```
.<predicate_prefix>_<property>_<operator>(value)
```

#### String Properties

| Operator | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `_is(v)` | exact match |
| `_is_not(v)` | exclude exact |
| `_in(vec)` | match any in list |
| `_not_in(vec)` | exclude list |
| `_containing(v)` / `_contains(v)` | substring (thing / human) |
| `_not_containing(v)` / `_not_contains(v)` | exclude substring |
| `_starting_with(v)` / `_starts_with(v)` | prefix (thing / human) |
| `_ending_with(v)` / `_ends_with(v)` | suffix (thing / human) |
| `_greater_than(v)` | lexicographic > |
| `_less_than(v)` | lexicographic < |
| `_between(a, b)` | lexicographic range |
| `_is_unknown()` | NULL check |

#### Number Properties

| Operator | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `_is(v)` | exact match |
| `_is_not(v)` | exclude exact |
| `_in(vec)` | match any in list |
| `_not_in(vec)` | exclude list |
| `_greater_than(v)` | `>` |
| `_greater_than_or_equal_to(v)` | `>=` |
| `_less_than(v)` | `<` |
| `_less_than_or_equal_to(v)` | `<=` |
| `_between(a, b)` | inclusive range |

#### DateTime Properties

All Number operators **plus**:

| Operator | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `_before(v)` | earlier than |
| `_after(v)` | later than |

#### ID Properties

| Operator | Example |
|----------|---------|
| `_is(v)` | exact match |
| `_is_not(v)` | exclude exact |
| `_in(vec)` | match any in list |
| `_not_in(vec)` | exclude list |

