### 3. Human vs Thing Naming Convention

Entities are classified as **Human** or **Thing**. This affects the predicate
prefixes and verb suffixes used in filter method names.

| Aspect | Thing | Human |
|--------|-------|-------|
| Attribute prefix | `with_` | `whose_` |
| Boolean prefix | `which_are_` | `who_are_` |
| String verb suffix | `-ing` (e.g. `_containing`) | `-s` (e.g. `_contains`) |

**Examples:**

```rust
// Thing entity (e.g. Order)
Q::orders()
    .with_title_containing("urgent")
    .which_are_active()

// Human entity (e.g. User)
Q::users()
    .whose_name_contains("Alice")
    .who_are_verified()
```

