### 4. Entity Instance Methods (per property)

For every property `p` on an entity instance, the following methods are available:

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `.p()` | Getter — returns the current value of `p` |
| `.update_p(value)` | Updater — sets a new value (change is tracked) |
| `.changed_p()` | Check — returns `true` if `p` was modified |

```rust
let name = user.name();           // getter
user.update_name("New Name");     // tracked update
if user.changed_name() {          // change detection
    // handle change
}
```

