### 8. Native Expression Safety (`eval_xxx`)

The system uses a highly optimized, zero-cost abstraction for navigating entity relationships safely without causing panics or requiring expensive `.clone()` operations. 

Instead of directly accessing properties that might not be loaded from the database, always use the `eval_{property}` methods combined with `.and_then()` for deep graph traversals:

```rust
let result = task.eval_status()
    .and_then("status", |s| s.eval_name());

match result {
    teaql_core::eval::EvalResult::Value(val) => { /* use the loaded value */ },
    teaql_core::eval::EvalResult::Null => { /* legitimately empty */ },
    teaql_core::eval::EvalResult::NotLoaded { missing_path } => {
        // AI RULE: If you encounter NotLoaded, your SelectQuery failed to fetch this path!
        // You MUST update your query to `.select("path.to.missing_property")` and retry.
    }
}
```

This ensures compile-time safety (no unexpected null pointers) and perfect runtime context for self-healing queries.

